🚀 Getting Started

#Prerequisites
1. Node.js installed (v18+ recommended)
2. MongoDB running locally or a MongoDB Atlas cloud URI
3. A Google AI Studio API Key (for the Gemini model)

Installation & Setup
1. Clone the Repository
Begin by cloning the repository from GitHub and navigating into the project's root directory:

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
git clone https://github.com/theabhishek339/ai-job-prep-web-app.git
cd ai-job-prep-web-app
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Backend Configuration & Startup
Navigate into the Backend folder, install the necessary dependencies, and set up your environment variables.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
cd Backend
npm install
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Create a file named .env inside the Backend directory and populate it with your local configurations:

***************************CODE SNIPPET*************************
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_key
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_google_gemini_api_key
Once the environment variables are set, boot up the server using the development script (configured with nodemon):

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
npm run dev
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Note: The backend server should now be running, typically at http://localhost:5000.

3. Frontend Configuration & Startup

Open a new terminal window or tab, return to the project root, navigate into the Frontend folder, and spin up the Vite development server.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
cd Frontend
npm install
npm run dev
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. Access the Application
Once Vite finishes compiling the assets, it will output a local URL in your terminal (usually http://localhost:5173). Open that link in your browser to interact with your AI Mock Interview Simulator.
